OL,3,CThames Water should be allowed to
OL,4,C'collapse and start again', Oxford MP
OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FThe government should allow Thames
OL,8,FWater to collapse rather than
OL,9,Fpermitting a rescue deal to go ahead,
OL,10,Faccording to an Oxfordshire MP.
OL,12,FLayla Moran argues that Britain's
OL,13,Fbiggest water company "is not fit for
OL,14,Fpurpose nor viable" - adding that any
OL,15,Fprivate bailout would "just delay the
OL,16,Finevitable" failure of the firm.
OL,26,@uD@WOUvD@SO]wD@WOUxD@KO]
