OL,3,CThames Water should be allowed to
OL,4,C'collapse and start again', Oxford MP
OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FIt is understood consultants have been
OL,8,Fbrought in to advise ministers on
OL,9,Fcontingency planning for special
OL,10,Fadministration. Government sources say
OL,11,Fthere would be no disruption to
OL,12,Fcustomers' water supply because of the
OL,13,Ffinancial position of any utility
OL,14,Fcompany.
